  "title": "Center of mass of two falling blocks",
  "content": {
    "prompt": "<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents two blocks labeled arranged horizontally. The block on the left is labeled M, and the block on the right is labeled 3 M. A horizontal string extends from the right side of the left block, M, to the left side of the right block, 3 M.\" height=\"71\" src=\"/images/6d83b96895ef0067824c579f56471d1b.png\" width=\"255\"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A block of mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"M\"><math alttext=\"M\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>M</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> and a block of mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"3 M\"><math alttext=\"3 M\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>M</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> are connected by a string, as shown above. The blocks are held with the string horizontally and are released from rest at the same time from a height <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"H\"><math alttext=\"H\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>H</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> above the ground. How does the acceleration of the center of mass of the system compare to the acceleration of the object of mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"M\"><math alttext=\"M\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>M</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> ?</p>\n",
    "answer": "i3",
    "choices": [
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The acceleration of the center of mass is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"4\"><math alttext=\"4\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>4</mn></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> times the acceleration of the object of mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"M\"><math alttext=\"M\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>M</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>.</p>",
        "value": "i1"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The acceleration of the center of mass is one fourth the acceleration of the object of mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"M\"><math alttext=\"M\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>M</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>.</p>",
        "value": "i2"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The acceleration of the center of mass is the same as the acceleration of the object of mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"M\"><math alttext=\"M\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>M</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>.</p>",
        "value": "i3"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The acceleration of the center of mass is initially <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"4\"><math alttext=\"4\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>4</mn></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> times smaller than the acceleration of the object of mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"3 M\"><math alttext=\"3 M\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>M</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, but the accelerations are the same after a long time.</p>",
        "value": "i4"
      }
    ]
  },
